rce/Dr._Dre\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Dr Dre\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dr._Dre\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dr._Dre\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The closing spectacle marked the beginning of the four-year countdown to the LA Games, and Americangymnastics icon Simone Bilesjoined Los Angeles Mayor Karen Bass as the Olympic flag was formally handed over.\", \"from\": 912, \"to\": 1120, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1046, \"end\": 1057, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1435544043842467e-13, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}, {\"begin\": 1064, \"end\": 1074, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Karen_Bass\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Karen Bass\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Karen_Bass\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Karen_Bass\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Earlier, International Olympic Committee president Thomas Bach described the Paris Games as \\\"sport at its best\\\".\", \"from\": 1122, \"to\": 1234, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1131, \"end\": 1162, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 1173, \"end\": 1184, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Bach\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Thomas Bach\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Bach\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Bach\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"These were sensational Olympic Games from start to finish,\\\" Bach said.\", \"from\": 1236, \"to\": 1307, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1297, \"end\": 1301, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Johann_Sebastian_Bach\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.367947216413637e-16, \"text\": \"Bach\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Johann_Sebastian_Bach\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Johann_Sebastian_Bach\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Or dare I say: Seine-sational Games,\\\" the IOC chief quipped about the Seine River where the opening ceremony unfolded and the triathlon and marathon swimming events took place.\", \"from\": 1308, \"to\": 1485, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1351, \"end\": 1354, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.361896166909136e-32, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At what will be Bach's last games after announcing his intention to step down next year, the IOC chief also called for \\\"a culture of peace\\\" in a war-torn world.\", \"from\": 1487, \"to\": 1647, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1503, \"end\": 1507, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Johann_Sebastian_Bach\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.367947216413637e-16, \"text\": \"Bach\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Johann_Sebastian_Bach\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Johann_Sebastian_Bach\"}, {\"begin\": 1580, \"end\": 1583, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.361896166909136e-32, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We know that the Olympic Games cannot create peace, but the Olympic Games can create a culture of peace that inspires the world,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 1649, \"to\": 1788, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Let us live this culture of peace every single day.\\\"\", \"from\": 1789, \"to\": 1842, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"About 9,000 athletes danced and sang the night away during the closing ceremony, which was billed as a celebration of humanity and the unifying power of sport.\", \"from\": 1844, \"to\": 2003, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We knew you would be brilliant, but you were magic,\\\" Paris 2024 organising chief Tony Estanguet told athletes.\", \"from\": 2005, \"to\": 2116, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2087, \"end\": 2101, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tony_Estanguet\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tony Estanguet\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tony_Estanguet\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tony_Estanguet\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"You made us happy, you made us feel alive - the world needed this moment so much.\\\"\", \"from\": 2117, \"to\": 2200, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The ceremony began with Leon Marchand, who won four gold medals in swimming for France, collecting the Olympic flame from the cauldron in the Tuileries Gardens to begin its journey to the stadium.\", \"from\": 2202, \"to\": 2398, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2231, \"end\": 2239, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brad_Marchand\", \"score\": 0.9999967930567927, \"rank\": 1.8285474037141585e-06, \"text\": \"Marchand\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q11774891\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brad_Marchand\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brad_Marchand\"}, {\"begin\": 2282, \"end\": 2288, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9924810248252565, \"rank\": 0.006939723062622882, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Reappearing later in the stadium to chants of \\\"L\\u00e9on, L\\u00e9on\\\", Marchand blew out the flame.\", \"from\": 2400, \"to\": 2488, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The ceremony followed 17 days of frequently breathtaking\\u00a0sporting action set against the backdrop of iconic Parisian landmarks from the Eiffel Tower to the Chateau de Versailles.\", \"from\": 2490, \"to\": 2668, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2646, \"end\": 2667, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palace_of_Versailles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Chateau de Versailles\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palace_of_Versailles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palace_of_Versailles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In contrast to the rain-soaked opening ceremony, Sunday's celebration in the national stadium began as a golden sunset bathed the French capital.\", \"from\": 2670, \"to\": 2815, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2800, \"end\": 2806, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.7627021359062496, \"rank\": 0.20027873241427602, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"China and the United States battled for the top spot up until the final day when the US women's basketball teamsqueezed past France67-66 to clinch the last gold of Paris 2024.\", \"from\": 2817, \"to\": 2992, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2817, \"end\": 2822, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9970224235906049, \"rank\": 0.0029469232715709903, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\"